## üõ°Ô∏è Exercise: SSH Session Termination Audit
Monitoring when and where sessions are closed is critical for identifying session hijacking or automated malicious activity.

**Command executed:**
```bash
grep "closed by" /var/log/auth.log | awk -F" " '{print "Access Date:" $1 "| Host:", $2}'

I transformed the raw system logs into a structured format for better readability:

Log Output	Analysis
Access Date: 2026-02-18T18:08:24...	Precise timestamp of the session termination.
Host: cs-11673031153-default	Identification of the specific asset (Google Cloud Shell instance).

